# Fluff Date: 2026-02-28 17:47:08
overview:<p>The Timber Wolf is a 75-ton Clan heavy OmniMech introduced in 2945 by Clan Wolf, designed as part of a second-generation OmniMech triad alongside the Gargoyle and Naga to replace the aging Woodsman. Where the Gargoyle provided speed and the Naga offered fire-support capability, the Timber Wolf represented a near-perfect synthesis of firepower, protection, and mobility that instantly established it as the most coveted OmniMech in Clan space. Clan Wolf jealously guarded production rights to the design, successfully defending them through numerous Trials of Possession, and until the Clan Invasion of the Inner Sphere in 3049, manufacturing was limited to a single facility on Strana Mechty.</p><p>Designated "Mad Cat" by Inner Sphere forces after a targeting computer alternated between Marauder and Catapult identification codes when first attempting to classify the unknown design, the Timber Wolf has since become the most recognizable symbol of Clan military power and remains one of the most feared OmniMechs ever produced.</p>

capabilities:<p>Built on a Type W3 Endo Steel chassis and powered by a Starfire 375 XL engine, the Timber Wolf achieves a maximum speed of 86 kph, exceptional for a heavy OmniMech. Twelve tons of Composite A-2 Ferro-Fibrous armor provide protection approaching that of many assault-class designs, though a notable weakness exists in the cockpit canopy area, where exceptionally large ferroglass viewports offer below-average ballistic protection to the MechWarrior. The chassis dedicates 27.5 tons to pod space, providing commanders with extraordinary flexibility in tailoring the design to mission requirements.</p><p>In its Primary configuration, the Timber Wolf mounts a devastating combination of energy and missile weaponry that is effective across all engagement ranges. A pair of ER Large Lasers and twin LRM-20 racks form the backbone of its long-range firepower, capable of stripping armor from targets at extreme distances. As engagements close, two ER Medium Lasers, a Medium Pulse Laser, and a pair of Machine Guns provide withering short-range fire. Fifteen double heat sinks manage the considerable thermal output, though sustained alpha strikes will test even this capacity. The Khan Series communications system and Series III OPT targeting and tracking system provide the MechWarrior with enhanced battlefield awareness and improved accuracy at medium ranges.</p><p>The Timber Wolf's true strength lies in the synergy between its speed, firepower, and armor. It can dictate engagement ranges against slower opponents while carrying enough armament to threaten designs well above its weight class. This combination proved devastating during Operation Revival, where Inner Sphere forces found themselves facing a heavy OmniMech that could outmaneuver their medium designs while outgunning their assaults.</p>

deployment:<p>Alternate Configuration N blends elements of both the Primary and D configurations into a versatile combat package introduced during the ilClan era. Each arm carries an ER PPC for long-range direct fire, while LRM-15 racks in the side torsos provide sustained missile bombardment. Paired Machine Guns and Medium Pulse Lasers in each side torso create a devastating short-range defensive screen. Two tons of LRM reloads and a half ton of machine gun ammunition place emphasis on the energy weapons for sustained engagements, with an extra double heat sink helping manage the considerable thermal output.</p>

history:<p>The Timber Wolf was born from Clan Wolf's ambitious program to replace the first-generation Woodsman OmniMech with three specialized successors. Entering production in 2945 at Wolf Clan Site #2 on Strana Mechty, the design immediately proved its worth in Clan Trials, and every Clan quickly recognized its extraordinary potential. Clan Wolf successfully defended exclusive production rights through a long series of Trials of Possession, ensuring that other Clans could only acquire the design through trade, gifts, or battlefield salvage. This monopoly made the Timber Wolf a powerful bargaining chip in inter-Clan politics and a symbol of Wolf dominance throughout the Golden Century and beyond.</p><p>The Timber Wolf's reputation was cemented during Operation Revival in 3049, when it became the first Clan OmniMech encountered by Inner Sphere forces. The Fourth Wolf Guard and Thirteenth Cruiser Cluster deployed the design to devastating effect, and ComStar analysts struggled to classify a machine that defied everything they understood about BattleMech design. Inner Sphere MechWarriors found their equipment woefully inferior when facing the Timber Wolf, and the design quickly came to symbolize the Clans' overwhelming technical superiority. Much of Clan Wolf's success during the invasion was built on the Timber Wolf's dominance of the battlefield.</p><p>The Timber Wolf continued to see extensive service through the Refusal War and into the era of the Word of Blake Jihad, remaining the premier frontline OmniMech of Clan Wolf's touman. However, the design's fortunes shifted dramatically following the Wars of Reaving, which severed ties between the Inner Sphere Clans and the Homeworlds. The Wolf Clan Site #2 on Strana Mechty passed through Clan Coyote ownership during the Jihad era and eventually fell to uncertain Clan control. Meanwhile, WC Site 1 on Arc-Royal, which had produced the Timber Wolf since the Civil War era, was destroyed during the Blakist assault in 3072, dealing a devastating blow to the Wolves' production capacity.</p><p>By 3080, the surviving W-7 Facilities on Weingarten were reduced to building Timber Wolves by hand, with some components individually machined due to missing manufacturing data evacuated from the Homeworlds. Attrition vastly outstripped supply, and the Wolves increasingly turned to other designs to fill their depleted ranks. The Timber Wolf's fortunes only recovered when Alaric Ward forged the Wolf Empire. Leaving the W-7 Facilities to Clan Hell's Horses, Ward ordered the Kallon Weapon Industries plant on Thermopolis retooled for Timber Wolf production, restoring the iconic design to prominence within the Wolf touman. The Kallon facility, operational by the ilClan era, ensured the Timber Wolf would remain the symbol of Clan Wolf's martial identity for generations to come.</p>

